<paragraph id="8B8736E9245550416BEFFCBCF0DBFC61" blockId="14.[131,777,591,922]" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">
DISTRIBUTION AND HABITAT. — 
<taxonomicName id="4C384D6A245550416AA7FCBFF3DFFC9E" authorityName="Capuron &amp; Sleumer" authorityYear="1972" box="[460,678,845,869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Scolopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis id="B94CEAFB245550416AA7FCBFF3DFFC9E" box="[460,678,845,869]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">Scolopia septentrionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from two collections from a single locality, the Sahafary forest, in the extreme north (
<figureCitation id="13032A6C245550416A37FC70F0ECFC61" box="[348,405,898,922]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[813,824,1260,1278]" captionTargetBox="[812,1456,214,1218]" captionTargetId="figure-785@8.[804,1465,194,1224]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 5. — Distribution of Scolopia erythrocarpa H.Perrier (●), S. hazomby H.Perrier (▲), and S. septentrionalis Capuron &amp; Sleumer (■)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4598927" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4598927/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3226562245550416BEFFC27F0E4FB75" pageId="14" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8736E9245550416BEFFC27F191FC16" blockId="14.[130,775,981,1167]" box="[132,232,981,1007]" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8736E9245550416BEFFC06F0E4FB75" blockId="14.[130,775,981,1167]" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName id="4C384D6A245550416BEFFC06F012FBF5" authorityName="Capuron &amp; Sleumer" authorityYear="1972" box="[132,363,1012,1038]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Scolopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis id="B94CEAFB245550416BEFFC06F012FBF5" box="[132,363,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">Scolopia septentrionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a large shrub or small tree (“arbuste”); the fruit may be reddish. It may be distinguished from other species of the single-flowered xerophytic group by its small and narrow leaves; it also has far fewer stamens than 
<taxonomicName id="4C384D6A2455504169DEFBA6F1D5FB75" authorityName="Capuron &amp; Sleumer" authorityYear="1972" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Scolopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calcicola">
<emphasis id="B94CEAFB2455504169DEFBA6F1D5FB75" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">S. calcicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs nearby.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3226562245550416BEFFB47F365FA55" pageId="14" pageNumber="113" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8B8736E9245550416BEFFB47F002FB37" blockId="14.[130,776,1205,1454]" box="[132,379,1205,1231]" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">CONSERVATION STATUS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8736E9245550416BEFFB26F365FA55" blockId="14.[130,776,1205,1454]" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">
The preliminary assessment of the conservation status of 
<taxonomicName id="4C384D6A2455504169DFFB26F074FAF6" authorityName="Capuron &amp; Sleumer" authorityYear="1972" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Scolopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis id="B94CEAFB2455504169DFFB26F074FAF6" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">Scolopia septentrionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is Critically Endangered (CR B1ab(iii)+B2ab(iii)). With an Extent of Occurrence of 
<quantity id="4CC09B0C24555041696AFAE1F334FAD6" box="[513,589,1299,1325]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="113" unit="km" value="16.0">16 km</quantity>
2 and an Area of Occupancy of less than 
<quantity id="4CC09B0C245550416AE6FAC1F0AAFAB6" box="[397,467,1331,1357]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="113" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
2, 
<taxonomicName id="4C384D6A245550416A87FAC6F3E2FAB6" authorityName="Capuron &amp; Sleumer" authorityYear="1972" box="[492,667,1331,1358]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Scolopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis id="B94CEAFB245550416A87FAC6F3E2FAB6" box="[492,667,1331,1358]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">S. septentrionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from only a single location, the Sahafary forest, which is unprotected and subject to continuing degradation. It has not been recollected for almost fifty years.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
